  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">FUAD ACT Alliance IRQ161 Support to IDPs and their hosts including Mosul</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the ACT Iraq IRQ161 programme is to alleviate suffering and build the resilience of internally displaced persons and vulnerable host communities in Iraq by improving access to essential assistance and recovery activities. Specifically, this will achieved through the provision of shelter/NFIs, WASH items, food packages, cash assistance, and increasing access to education, livelihoods and protection and psychosocial support.  

This initial funding received will provide hygiene kits and WASH awareness raising to non-camp IDPs from Mosul residing in Al Shirqat, Salah ah Din. This initial funding will target 1039 families.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is part of the ACT IRQ161 appeal in Iraq. This project will bring about significant change to the lives of those in Iraq affected by the most recent humanitarian crisis, specifically  the needs of Mosul IDPs in Al Shirqat. Assessment has been carried out by FUAD.</narrative>
  </description>
